Description: CVE-2026-6653 - fix use-after-free in xmlParseInternalSubset
 A use-after-free was possible in xmlParseInternalSubset() because
 inputPush() freed its 'value' argument when the inputTab realloc failed,
 while the caller (xmlPushInput / xmlParsePEReference) also freed it.
 The double-free left a freed xmlParserInputPtr in ctxt->input, which
 xmlParseInternalSubset later dereferenced (heap-UAF READ at parser.c
 ctxt->input->consumed).
 .
 The upstream fix is part of a large structural rework of the entity
 amplification accounting (libxml2 commit 463bbeeca, v2.11.0), which
 introduces new public ABI fields and helper functions not available in
 2.9.10. To avoid an ABI break in Debian bullseye, this is a
 minimal-touch backport that only addresses the underlying double-free
 in inputPush(): on realloc failure inputPush() no longer frees 'value'
 and instead leaves ownership with the caller, matching the contract
 already implemented at every call site (xmlPushInput, xmlParsePEReference,
 xmlParseStringPEReference, etc., which all call xmlFreeInputStream(input)
 themselves on error).
 .
 With the spurious free removed, the error path in xmlParsePEReference
 frees the input exactly once and ctxt->input is no longer left
 dangling, eliminating the UAF reported as CVE-2026-6653.
Origin: backport, https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libxml2/-/commit/463bbeeca1805b5c4828f50d0fefc4eebaf620df
Bug: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/libxml2/-/issues/605
Author: Nick Wellnhofer <wellnhofer@aevum.de>
Last-Update: 2026-06-22

--- a/parser.c
+++ b/parser.c
@@ -1725,9 +1725,7 @@ inputPush(xmlParserCtxtPtr ctxt, xmlParserInputPtr value)
                                              sizeof(ctxt->inputTab[0]));
         if (ctxt->inputTab == NULL) {
             xmlErrMemory(ctxt, NULL);
-	    xmlFreeInputStream(value);
 	    ctxt->inputMax /= 2;
-	    value = NULL;
             return (-1);
         }
     }
