+## ✅ Recommendations
+
+### For All Environments
+
+- ✅ **Ignore CVE-2025-12863 entirely**: It's officially rejected and not a real vulnerability  
+- ✅ **Update scanner databases**: Ensure your security scanning tools sync with the latest CVE feeds  
+- ✅ **Configure exceptions**: Add CVE-2025-12863 to your scanner's ignore/suppression list  
+- ✅ **Document the rejection**: Reference the official NVD rejection in your security reports
+
+### Scanner Configuration Examples
+
+**Trivy** (`.trivyignore` file):
+```
+# CVE-2025-12863 - Officially REJECTED by NVD on 2025-11-20
+# Reference: https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-12863
+CVE-2025-12863
+```
+
+
+### Best Practices
+
+- 🔄 **Keep scanner databases updated**: Ensure regular synchronization with CVE feeds  
+- 📝 **Maintain an exceptions list**: Document all suppressed CVEs with justification  
+- 🛡️ **Focus on real vulnerabilities**: Don't waste time on rejected CVEs  
+- 📊 **Report scanner issues**: If your scanner doesn't respect REJECTED status, report it to the vendor
+
+---
+
+## 🧷 Summary
+
+- **CVE-2025-12863** is a **rejected CVE** - it was deemed **NOT a valid vulnerability** by the CVE authority  
+- The original report of a use-after-free in `xmlSetTreeDoc()` was investigated and found to be incorrect  
+- Any security scanner flagging this CVE is using **outdated CVE databases**  
+- There is **zero risk** associated with this CVE because it doesn't represent a real security issue  
